Permission is granted to the AI for Impact Challenge organisers, judges,
coaches, and authorised University of Zimbabwe reviewers to access, run,
inspect, test, and reproduce the software and public-safe evidence in this
repository for challenge evaluation, education, technical review, and
institutional pilot planning.

No permission is granted to:

1. redistribute the confidential University of Zimbabwe source dataset;
2. infer or publish private facility, meter, account, or tariff information;
3. use the software to control mains-connected equipment without qualified
   engineering review and institutional authorisation;
4. represent public-source planning estimates as actual bills or realised
   savings;
5. represent the prototype as a commissioned production deployment.

The software and evidence are provided "as is", without warranty of any kind,
including fitness for electrical control, billing, safety-critical operation,
or production deployment.

Third-party packages remain subject to their own licences. The supplied study
figures and institutional evidence remain subject to their source and data-use
conditions.
